result.execSummary:
The defendant Saxon T. Henry was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Saxon T. Henry is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Saxon T. Henry was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
